subproject.description:
The main objectives of TPMP in Zambia are as follows:

1)	To enable the Government to phase-out its CFC consumption in accordance with the phase out targets of the Montreal Protocol. 
2)	To achieve the CFC phase-out without compromising the performance or effectiveness of the refrigeration system in Zambia;
3)	To minimise the economic impact of the country of achieving the CFC phase-out;
4)	To eliminate over a period of three years 2008–2010, the remaining consumption of CFC in Zambia;
5)	To ensure that measure are in place to sustain not only CFC phase-out, but also sustain zero consumption of CFCs.
